---
title: Mushroom Lover’s Gnocchi with Garlicky Panko & Parmesan
description: Treat yourself to truffles with tonight’s ‘shroom-packed pasta. You’ll start with tender, pillowy mushroom gnocchi, then toss them in a silky sauce of sautéed button mushrooms, mushroom stock, cream cheese, and Parmesan. A swirl of butter and dusting of truffle zest take the rich umami flavors to the next level. Garnish everything with crunchy, garlicky panko, then pour yourself a glass of wine and toast to a restaurant-worthy dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mushroom-lover-s-gnocchi-efc82007.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mushroom-lover-s-gnocchi-61795acf56e6435c1538f518-03cb69ce.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mushroom-lovers-gnocchi-61795acf56e6435c1538f518
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 620 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 61 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1380 mg
course: main course
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{}(for boiling) salted with @salt{} to a boil. Wash
and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Quarter @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}; cook, stirring, until golden and toasted,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later). Cook until
just fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium.

Once mushrooms are browned and tender, add @mushroom gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to pot
of boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), scallion whites, and remaining
garlic powder into pan with mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/3%cup} (½ cup for 4), @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @cream
cheese{4%tablespoon}, and half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup} (save the rest for
serving). Cook, stirring, until combined and creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off
heat.

Stir in tomatoes, another @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), and
@truffle zest{2%g} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir drained gnocchi into pan with sauce until thoroughly coated, adding water
a splash at a time as needed.

Divide between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan.
Sprinkle with as much garlicky panko as you like and serve.